# Connection Finder — environment configuration.
# Copy to ".env" and fill in whatever you have. The tool degrades gracefully:
# it uses every provider whose key is present and ignores the rest. You need
# AT LEAST ONE search provider configured.

# --- Search providers (configure one or more) ---
# Brave Search API (recommended default; generous free tier, clean JSON):
#   https://brave.com/search/api/
BRAVE_API_KEY=

# Google Programmable Search Engine (Custom Search JSON API). Needs BOTH:
#   https://programmablesearchengine.google.com/  (gives the cx / CSE id)
#   https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/overview  (gives the key)
GOOGLE_CSE_ID=
GOOGLE_CSE_KEY=

# Bing Web Search v7 (Azure). NOTE: Microsoft has announced retirement of the
# Bing Search APIs — only set this if you still hold a working key.
BING_API_KEY=

# --- Extraction LLM (optional) ---
# With a Gemini key, extraction quality is high. Without it, the tool falls
# back to a no-LLM heuristic extractor (lower confidence, but still works).
#   https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
